### Malapportionment

https://sci-hub.box/10.2139/ssrn.3048551

"Malapportionment is the creation of electoral districts with dissimilar ratios of voters to representatives. In practice, it amplifies the influence of voters in districts with fewer votes and dilutes the influence of voters in districts with larger numbers of voters."

The EIP ranks Malaysia's electoral boundaries as the most biased of the 155 countries assessed. 

"The 2013 general election illustrates this clearly, as malapportionment translated the BN’s 4% popular vote deficit into a 20% advantage in parliamentary  seats."


Electoral Integrity Project's Global Perceptions of Electoral Integrity

